"I'llI'll think about it," was my answer,
                        in a tone which I hoped she would see was not hesitating, but reflective;
                        "I mustn't go too far,or too fast."

He thought a long time, and I did not try to hurry him. At length he said, in
                        his old off-hand manner: "Well, I'll go you, Senator;
                        I'll not touch a drop."
